&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fixed Term Only&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a fixed term post for 6 months due to funding. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you are a Swansea Bay University Health Board employee this post will only be offered on a secondment basis and you will need to have gained your line managers approval for the secondment before applying.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Medicines Management Team (Domiciliary Care) are looking to recruit a Health Care Support Worker to assist the team with provision of care to individuals in the community and hospital sites, supporting the Swansea MAR scheme and Hospital 2 Home project. The post holder will undertake the provision of identified needs and duties to enable patients to remain at home and participate in consistent high quality care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gaye BrownMedicines Management Team Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;gaye.brown@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01792 517978 Mobile: 07814 928216&lt;/p&gt;
